Odaily Planet Daily News According to @defioasis data from Dune, in the past six months, among the 4.257 million addresses with more than 10 transactions of pump fun tokens, more than 60% of the addresses have realized losses; 
2.408 million addresses (accounting for 56.6%) have accumulated losses between $0 and $1,000; 
About 1,700 addresses have losses of more than $100,000, of which 46 addresses have losses of more than $1 million. 
In terms of cumulative profits, $0-1,000 is the most widely distributed range, reaching 916,500 addresses (accounting for 21.5%); 
More than 5,000 addresses have profits of more than $100,000, of which about 310 addresses have profits of more than $1 million.

Odaily Planet Daily News: Tim Draper, a well-known Silicon Valley investor, posted on the X platform that he still insists on the prediction that Bitcoin can reach $250,000 this year. The main factors driving the development of Bitcoin at this stage are: 
1. Trump reached a trade agreement and the market is generally optimistic; 
2. The regulatory framework expected by the industry is about to be introduced; 
3. Web3 applications built on the Bitcoin blockchain continue to develop. 
Tim Draper added that major banks are adding Bitcoin to their products, and even JPMorgan Chase, which has long refused to provide encryption services, plans to join soon. As companies flock in, Bitcoin will become more mainstream. In addition, compared with other cryptocurrencies and stocks, Bitcoin has lower risks because people believe in Bitcoin, which also makes Bitcoin win the title of a means of value storage.
